title: Motorhead 1975-07-20 Roundhouse - FIRST-EVER GIG
description:
July 1975. Lemmy, fresh from leaving Hawkwind, starts a band and calls it Motorhead. This is their first show, support act. No &#039;Ace of Spades&#039; or stuff like that to fill the set-list, so he raided the Hawkwind music vault.

Reseed from Dime on 10 May 2008, by Dime&#039;s sonic_hawk

Thanx to Dime&#039;s stevem1 for seeding it.

01  Introduction
02  Motorhead
03  Leaving Here
04  Good Morning Little Schoolgirl
05  Lost Johnny
06  City Kids
07  Silver Machine
    Waiting For The Man

I haven&#039;t split Silver and Waiting because I think they&#039;re ok as they are, a sort of segue.
